    "description": "A pickler object’s dispatch table is a registry of reduction functions of the kind which can be declared using copyreg.pickle(). It is a mapping whose keys are classes and whose values are reduction functions. A reduction function takes a single argument of the associated class and should conform to the same interface as a __reduce__() method. By default, a pickler object will not have a dispatch_table attribute, and it will instead use the global dispatch table managed by the copyreg module....",
